<p>
  When working with APIs, email templates, or web applications, you often encounter images stored as Base64 strings. This guide shows you how to decode a Base64 string back to a viewable, downloadable image — for free, in seconds.
</p>

<h2>What Does Base64 Look Like?</h2>

<p>A Base64 image string looks like this (truncated for readability):</p>
<pre><code>data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUA
AAAFCAYAAACNbyblAAAAHElEQVQI12P4
BCAmvA8ABGABCK/AAAAAElFTkSuQmCC</code></pre>

<p>It may also appear without the prefix (raw Base64 only):</p>
<pre><code>iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUA...</code></pre>

<h2>How to Decode Base64 to an Image Online</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the <a href="/imagewonder/base64-to-image">Base64 to Image decoder</a>.</li>
  <li>Paste your Base64 string (with or without the <code>data:image/...;base64,</code> prefix).</li>
