<h2>Decode Base64 to Image in JavaScript</h2>

<pre><code>// Display a Base64 string as an image
const base64 = 'iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUg...';
const img = document.createElement('img');
img.src = "data:image/png;base64," + base64;
document.body.appendChild(img);</code></pre>

<h2>Decode in Python</h2>

<pre><code>import base64

encoded = "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUg..."
image_data = base64.b64decode(encoded)
with open("output.png", "wb") as f:
    f.write(image_data)</code></pre>

<h2>Common Errors</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Corrupted/partial image:</strong> The Base64 string was truncated. Copy the full string from the source.</li>
  <li><strong>Wrong format:</strong> If you know the image is JPEG but see color issues, include the correct prefix: <code>data:image/jpeg;base64,</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>Extra whitespace:</strong> Some systems add line breaks to Base64 strings. Strip all newlines before decoding.</li>
</ul>

